Advanced Projects

## Introduction

This section focuses on building moderately advanced projects that apply programming concepts to solve practical and real-world problems. The goal is to strengthen problem-solving ability, improve code design, and gain hands-on experience with structured and scalable solutions. These projects demonstrate the transition from basic implementations to more thoughtful and efficient applications.

## Project Statements

K-Map Solver (2–4 Variables)
Implement a tool that simplifies Boolean expressions using Karnaugh Maps and outputs the minimized result.

Password Generator with Strength Checker
Generate random passwords and evaluate their strength based on multiple criteria such as length, symbols, and complexity.

## Note

This section highlights practical applications of programming concepts at a moderate level. Projects will be continuously refined with better features, improved efficiency, and cleaner code structure.
